WEBVTT

00:12.875 --> 00:13.834
TERRY:
Is that your boyfriend?

00:13.917 --> 00:15.333
BRIDGET:
I think so.

00:15.417 --> 00:17.333
MARVIN:
Hey, hey, Mr. Donovan.

00:17.417 --> 00:18.792
Hey, you buy me yet?

00:18.875 --> 00:20.250
RAY:
Remember that kid we bought?

00:20.333 --> 00:22.208
His mother must've shot off
her mouth.

00:22.291 --> 00:24.959
You promised me this wouldn't
come back.

00:25.041 --> 00:26.333
You promised me.

00:26.417 --> 00:28.458
EZRA: Sean shot the girl
with your gun,

00:28.542 --> 00:30.375
high on your drugs.

00:30.458 --> 00:31.333
Ray said you were
in trouble anyway--

00:31.417 --> 00:32.959
you'd stolen a lot of money
from Sully.

00:33.041 --> 00:34.917
Sean Walker really killed
that girl, huh?

00:35.000 --> 00:37.333
AVI:
Mickey's met with him

00:37.417 --> 00:40.041
a couple of times
since Palm Springs.

00:40.125 --> 00:42.667
(siren wailing)
You seem a little
under the weather.

00:42.750 --> 00:45.917
Ray? (shouts)
Motherfucker.

00:46.000 --> 00:48.750
If you think he's after you,
he probably is.

00:48.834 --> 00:50.792
RAY: You think you're
the first person that tried

00:50.875 --> 00:52.000
to shut us down, you dumb fuck?

00:52.083 --> 00:54.041
I told you everything.
I told you...

00:54.125 --> 00:55.750
Who the fuck are you, Ray?

00:55.834 --> 00:57.917
NOMI:
Is he a good husband?

00:58.000 --> 00:59.333
How do you mean?
Men are...
they're naturally

00:59.417 --> 01:01.834
really secretive animals.

01:01.917 --> 01:03.000
You never told me
how Bridget died.

01:04.417 --> 01:04.959
RAY:
She was high on drugs.

01:05.041 --> 01:07.792
She jumped off a roof.

01:07.875 --> 01:09.792
BRIDGET:
Daddy, please stop it!

01:09.875 --> 01:11.959
You might've had the balls
to put me away, kid,

01:12.041 --> 01:14.208
but shoot me? I don't think so.

01:44.583 --> 01:47.000
ABBY:
Ray, you up here?

01:48.917 --> 01:51.750
Where you going now?

01:51.834 --> 01:54.083
Boston.

01:54.166 --> 01:56.250
Boston?!

01:56.333 --> 01:58.834
Why the fuck are you going
to Boston?

01:58.917 --> 02:00.250
You pull a gun

02:00.333 --> 02:01.166
on youfather
in front of your children,

02:01.250 --> 02:03.834
and then you pack your shit
and leave?

02:03.917 --> 02:05.667
It's business.
You won't even let me

02:05.750 --> 02:07.125
take the kids home
to see my parents,

02:07.208 --> 02:09.333
and now all of a sudden
you're going back?

02:09.959 --> 02:12.667
Is this about Colleen?

02:12.750 --> 02:14.041
For Christ's sakes,

02:14.125 --> 02:15.917
Abs, she's been dead
for 20 years.

02:16.000 --> 02:17.583
Then why are you going back?

02:17.667 --> 02:21.333
I gotta see someone.

02:21.417 --> 02:23.542
But you won't tell me who?

02:26.834 --> 02:29.208
What the hell is
a Steampunk Wizard of Oz?

02:29.291 --> 02:32.000
It's The Wizard of Oz set in
the world of Victorian England

02:32.083 --> 02:33.333
where everything's, like,

02:33.417 --> 02:35.083
steam-powered and
industrialized.

02:35.166 --> 02:38.000
Sounds stupid. Why are you all
of a sudden into doing musicals?

02:38.083 --> 02:40.041
I thought you hated that shit.

02:46.583 --> 02:49.250
Morning.

03:01.375 --> 03:03.000
(sighs)

03:03.083 --> 03:04.375
So, what are you guys
doing today?

03:07.333 --> 03:08.917
Well, Bridget's auditioning
for this dumb play,

03:09.000 --> 03:11.166
and I've got soccer.

03:11.250 --> 03:13.291
Yeah? Sounds like a good day.

03:15.500 --> 03:17.750
You fuckin' knew?!

03:17.834 --> 03:20.083
You knew my moms was killed
and you ain't tell me?
All right.

03:20.166 --> 03:21.583
All right, all right. Calm down.
Let's go outside.

03:21.667 --> 03:23.333
She was murdered
in our own house.
Ray...

03:23.417 --> 03:25.834
Out. Right now.
Fuck you, man.
You knew.

03:25.917 --> 03:26.917
Daddy!
No, Ray...

03:27.000 --> 03:30.291
No...!
Stay there, Bridget.

03:30.375 --> 03:32.792
ABBY:
Bridget, just... just wait.

03:32.875 --> 03:34.166
ABBY:
Hold on. Ray...
Fuck off me.

03:34.250 --> 03:36.417
Mom, stop.
No!

03:37.834 --> 03:38.417
What the fuck is this?

03:38.500 --> 03:39.542
Bring a gun
in my house?

03:44.542 --> 03:45.083
You should've told me.

03:45.166 --> 03:47.709
Shut up and keep walking.

03:53.709 --> 03:56.667
Fucking crazy, man.
What were you thinking?

03:56.750 --> 04:00.166
(sighs)
Yo. Sorry about that, man.

04:00.250 --> 04:02.792
He got a text from his
little cousin about his mom.

04:02.875 --> 04:05.083
I mean, dead bodies in
the house for days.

04:05.166 --> 04:07.542
That was just nasty.

04:11.500 --> 04:12.417
Yo, you do that?

04:14.583 --> 04:16.667
Are you out
of your fuckin' mind?

04:16.750 --> 04:18.875
(chuckles)
Hey, look, my bad.

04:18.959 --> 04:20.667
I'm just wonderin'.

04:20.750 --> 04:24.000
You keep that kid away
from my daughter, you hear me?

04:25.000 --> 04:27.875
All right.

04:27.959 --> 04:30.000
(clicks tongue)

04:30.083 --> 04:30.375
(sniffs)

04:35.792 --> 04:37.417
Where you going?
To talk to Marvin.

04:37.500 --> 04:39.375
No, you're not.
You can't just order me
to not...

04:39.458 --> 04:41.625
You stay away from him,
you understand me?

04:41.709 --> 04:44.542
(sighs)

04:50.041 --> 04:52.208
You want to explain what the
hell that kid was talking about?

04:52.291 --> 04:54.166
It's nothing.
He's just upset.

04:54.250 --> 04:55.750
He said his
mother was murdered,

04:55.834 --> 04:57.500
said you knew something
about it.

04:57.583 --> 05:00.792
It's got nothing
to do with us, Abs.
Really?

05:00.875 --> 05:02.834
You're scaring me, Ray.

05:02.917 --> 05:04.792
The way you've been.

05:04.875 --> 05:06.375
You're fucking scaring me.

05:06.458 --> 05:09.500
Come on, Abs.
(sighs heavily)

05:15.542 --> 05:17.709
See you in a few days.

05:34.709 --> 05:35.375
MAN:
Hey.

05:35.458 --> 05:38.000
You wanted to see me?
Yes.

05:39.291 --> 05:41.750
Have a seat.
(clears throat)

05:44.834 --> 05:48.166
You did some work
on Ezra Goldman

05:48.250 --> 05:51.166
and Lee Drexler
a couple of years ago.

05:51.250 --> 05:54.750
Yeah. I couldn't get it
to stick.

05:54.834 --> 05:56.083
They're crafty guys.

05:56.166 --> 05:58.667
Wiretapping, extortion,
jury tampering.

05:58.750 --> 06:01.250
Criminal justice terrorists.
I want to bring
some new evidence

06:01.333 --> 06:01.959
to Brady.

06:02.041 --> 06:04.583
See if I can get funded.

06:04.667 --> 06:05.917
Okay. What do you got?

06:06.000 --> 06:07.875
Murder.

06:09.500 --> 06:10.917
Involving Sean Walker.

06:11.000 --> 06:13.041
Sean fucking Walker?

06:14.375 --> 06:16.000
Are you serious?
I have evidence

06:16.083 --> 06:18.709
that he shot a girl in Boston
20 years ago,

06:18.792 --> 06:23.625
and Ezra Goldman and Ray Donovan
covered it up.

06:23.917 --> 06:27.125
Wow.

06:28.417 --> 06:30.041
I'm in.

06:30.917 --> 06:32.083
AVI:
The Fed's been looking for him

06:32.166 --> 06:34.625
for 20 years, Ray.

06:34.709 --> 06:38.291
Do you think you can just fly
to Boston and find him?

06:38.375 --> 06:39.834
Why don't you let me

06:39.917 --> 06:41.333
take care of Mick?

06:41.417 --> 06:43.458
Because I need you on the
outside, not in prison.

06:43.542 --> 06:46.458
You know, rumor is...

06:46.542 --> 06:47.458
he's in Belfast.

06:47.542 --> 06:50.458
Sully didn't go
to fucking Ireland.

06:53.375 --> 06:56.000
He's a ghost, Ray.

06:56.083 --> 06:58.709
You're chasing
a fucking ghost.

06:58.792 --> 07:00.625
Story of my life.

07:00.709 --> 07:03.792
And even if you
do find him, what?

07:03.875 --> 07:06.250
Thanks for the ride.

07:11.917 --> 07:13.750
Be careful out there.

07:13.834 --> 07:15.625
WOMAN (over P.A.):
The white zone is for

07:15.709 --> 07:19.792
the immediate loading and
unloading of passengers only.

07:19.875 --> 07:22.333
(dramatic movie soundtrack
music playing)

07:25.375 --> 07:27.709
(panting)

07:56.208 --> 07:57.750
Amen, motherfucker.

08:06.709 --> 08:08.291
(sighs, groans)

08:15.250 --> 08:17.875
MICKEY: "Amen, motherfucker."
(chuckles)

08:17.959 --> 08:20.917
I fucking love that line.
Shh!

08:21.041 --> 08:25.917
♪ ♪

08:38.500 --> 08:40.834
♪ ♪

08:48.166 --> 08:50.625
(audience applauds)

08:52.583 --> 08:53.959
(whistles)

08:57.333 --> 08:59.750
(phone ringing)

09:02.750 --> 09:04.458
What'd you find out?

09:04.542 --> 09:06.625
FRANK:
You're right about Van.

09:06.709 --> 09:08.625
What's he got?

09:08.709 --> 09:10.208
Says he found a witness

09:10.291 --> 09:12.166
to testify to a cover-up
of a murder.

09:12.250 --> 09:13.500
Says he could

09:13.583 --> 09:16.041
take down you, Ezra
and Sean Walker.

09:16.125 --> 09:19.000
What do you want me
to do about it?

09:19.083 --> 09:21.709
Try to sit on him
till I get back to town.

09:25.375 --> 09:26.792
(audience applauding,
dramatic soundtrack playing)

09:26.875 --> 09:28.917
MICKEY: There-- Mickey Donovan!
That's my name.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.792
Right there. Consultant.

09:39.917 --> 09:41.750
Black Mass.

09:41.834 --> 09:47.291
This minor masterpiece
of the '90s action oeuvre

09:47.375 --> 09:50.000
laid the groundwork
for such films

09:50.083 --> 09:52.667
as Tarantino's Reservoir Dogs,

09:52.750 --> 09:54.500
Fincher's Seven;
It was also

09:54.583 --> 09:57.542
the film, as we know,
that introduced

09:57.625 --> 10:00.792
the world
to the great talent

10:00.875 --> 10:03.500
of our guest of honor
this evening,

10:03.583 --> 10:06.875
Sean Walker. Oh.
(chuckles)

10:06.959 --> 10:09.041
Hey, Sean!

10:09.125 --> 10:10.208
Sean! Hey, Sean!

10:10.291 --> 10:11.083
Thank you. Thank you.

10:11.166 --> 10:13.208
Thank you.

10:14.166 --> 10:16.291
Thank you.

10:16.375 --> 10:17.792
I'll be right back.

10:17.875 --> 10:19.667
Be right back!
He'll be right back!

10:28.458 --> 10:30.083
(phone rings)

10:31.041 --> 10:32.750
Yeah.

10:32.834 --> 10:34.500
SEAN:
Ray, your father's stalking me.

10:34.583 --> 10:36.375
What?

10:36.458 --> 10:39.083
He's at my screening, screaming
my name from the third row.

10:39.166 --> 10:40.500
You got a bodyguard there?

10:40.583 --> 10:42.250
Bodyguard? What's that gonna do?

10:42.333 --> 10:43.458
Just don't get near him.

10:43.542 --> 10:44.959
You know, I'm sick of this shit!

10:45.041 --> 10:46.041
You keep saying
you're gonna handle this,

10:46.125 --> 10:47.625
and nothing fucking happens!

10:47.709 --> 10:49.083
I am handling. What the hell...?
SEAN:
You know

10:49.166 --> 10:50.125
how many times
you have said that?

10:50.208 --> 10:51.041
He's a harmless old man.

10:51.125 --> 10:52.709
He likes movies.
What can I tell you?

10:52.792 --> 10:53.667
You know what?

10:53.750 --> 10:54.208
You're fucking fired.

10:54.291 --> 10:55.625
Don't do that.

10:55.709 --> 10:58.041
I'm one
of the most important people

10:58.125 --> 11:00.583
on the planet; I can deal
with this on my own, Ray.

11:00.667 --> 11:02.875
Don't get
any stupid ideas, Sean.

11:02.959 --> 11:04.875
You're not a character
in one of your movies.

11:08.709 --> 11:11.375
Asshole.

11:11.458 --> 11:14.083
Are you ready, Sean?

11:17.250 --> 11:20.000
(sniffing)

11:20.083 --> 11:22.500
(applause and whooping)

11:25.583 --> 11:28.041
Sorry about that.
I had to get the mic on.

11:28.125 --> 11:29.917
Reset it.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.291
All right.

11:31.375 --> 11:34.417
All right, uh,
let's start with questions.

11:34.500 --> 11:35.959
Uh, yes.

11:36.041 --> 11:36.583
You in the
glasses, yes.

11:36.667 --> 11:39.417
Thanks.
(clears throat)

11:39.500 --> 11:40.417
Thanks. (clears throat)

11:40.500 --> 11:42.792
Hi. Hi. Uh, my name is Sam.

11:42.875 --> 11:44.917
I'm a very huge fan
of everything you do,

11:45.000 --> 11:47.375
Thank you.
and I love your work so much.

11:47.458 --> 11:49.667
Yeah, yeah, I'm-I'm a great fan,
too. I'm a big fan.
And Black Mass...

11:49.750 --> 11:52.375
And I got an idea
for a movie you should do.

11:53.917 --> 11:54.750
It's about an unknown actor

11:54.834 --> 11:56.959
who comes to Boston
to act in a film,

11:57.041 --> 12:00.375
and he ends up shooting a
young woman in the head.

12:00.458 --> 12:02.291
And then he frames a working Joe

12:02.375 --> 12:04.375
from an honest family
for the murder.

12:04.458 --> 12:06.625
Sounds interesting.

12:06.709 --> 12:07.542
Yeah, I ain't done yet.

12:07.625 --> 12:10.458
You see,
this honest family man--

12:10.542 --> 12:13.625
he goes to jail for 20 years.

12:13.709 --> 12:15.083
And the young actor--

12:15.166 --> 12:17.291
he becomes the biggest
movie star in the world.

12:17.375 --> 12:20.333
What do you think?

12:20.417 --> 12:22.417
It sounds a... a bit...

12:22.500 --> 12:23.625
You want to buy it?

12:23.709 --> 12:25.792
I actually don't buy pitches...

12:25.875 --> 12:26.959
MAN:
Buy it!

12:27.041 --> 12:28.000
Yeah, buy it.

12:28.083 --> 12:29.875
Buy it! Buy it!

12:29.959 --> 12:32.083
CROWD (chanting):
Buy it! Buy it!

12:32.166 --> 12:33.792
Buy it! Buy it!

12:33.875 --> 12:34.250
Buy it! Buy it! Buy it...!

12:34.333 --> 12:36.625
(laughter)

12:36.709 --> 12:37.583
Okay. Okay.
Buy it! Buy it! Buy it!

12:37.667 --> 12:40.542
You're very convincing.

12:40.625 --> 12:42.709
All right.
I'm gonna give you my number.

12:42.792 --> 12:43.667
All right. Sam?

12:43.750 --> 12:46.000
Um, yes, uh,
Black Mass.

12:46.083 --> 12:48.834
Christian undertones,
religious, all that good stuff.

12:48.917 --> 12:51.375
Did you study
with the Catholic Church?

12:51.458 --> 12:53.583
Did you do anything with
the priest... the priesthood?

12:59.208 --> 13:01.834
(sighs)

13:05.083 --> 13:08.166
Hi.

13:08.250 --> 13:09.417
What you want?

13:09.500 --> 13:13.375
About your mom.

13:13.458 --> 13:16.166
I just wanted to tell you
how sorry I am.

13:16.250 --> 13:17.750
It's a terrible thing.

13:17.834 --> 13:19.333
Were you close?

13:19.417 --> 13:22.625
She was my mom.

13:24.333 --> 13:26.834
Look, if you ever need
to talk...

13:27.709 --> 13:30.834
I know you
don't know me

13:30.917 --> 13:34.250
so well, but...
if you need to talk.

13:36.166 --> 13:39.250
I'm here.

13:44.291 --> 13:46.458
She was a drug addict.

13:46.542 --> 13:49.041
Couldn't raise me herself,

13:49.125 --> 13:50.333
so she sold me.

13:50.417 --> 13:53.542
Knowing her,

13:53.625 --> 13:55.583
she probably bragged
about all the cash she got.

13:55.667 --> 13:59.041
Someone killed her for it.

13:59.125 --> 14:02.792
What does my husband have to do
with that?

14:02.875 --> 14:06.750
Ask him yourself.

14:21.041 --> 14:22.500
(footsteps approaching)

14:22.583 --> 14:24.959
Sit down, Eddie.

14:30.333 --> 14:32.125
I don't know
what happened.

14:32.208 --> 14:36.542
I picked Mickey up out of that
lineup, just like I told you.

14:36.625 --> 14:37.750
There's some money
you're after, it's gone.

14:37.834 --> 14:41.250
Give it to my mother.
Surgery.

14:41.333 --> 14:43.417
Macular degeneration.

14:43.500 --> 14:45.959
Relax. I'm here to see Sully.

14:46.041 --> 14:51.125
Sully? Sully died ten
years ago, in Belfast.

14:51.208 --> 14:54.834
Just tell him I'm here.

14:59.291 --> 15:01.417
Hey, Ray.

15:01.500 --> 15:03.458
Remember me?

15:03.542 --> 15:05.125
No.

15:14.041 --> 15:15.542
Yo.

15:15.625 --> 15:17.625
You want to make some music?

15:17.709 --> 15:20.041
You want to order some sushi?

15:22.875 --> 15:25.000
I'll tell you what.
Hit that.

15:25.083 --> 15:27.458
That's gonna make you
feel better.

15:29.875 --> 15:32.375
You know what?

15:32.458 --> 15:33.417
We're gonna
throw you a party tomorrow.

15:33.500 --> 15:34.750
Why?

15:34.834 --> 15:37.125
Celebrate your birthday.

15:37.208 --> 15:38.500
It ain't my birthday tomorrow.

15:38.583 --> 15:39.166
(laughs)

15:39.250 --> 15:41.166
It's your new birthday, son.

15:41.250 --> 15:43.166
You got a whole new life
ahead of you.

15:43.250 --> 15:45.458
So, chin up.

15:45.542 --> 15:48.041
We partying tomorrow.

15:48.125 --> 15:49.625
SPORTS ANNOUNCER: Halfway
through the tenth round now,

15:49.709 --> 15:51.291
both fighters beginning
to show signs of fatigue...

15:51.375 --> 15:53.375
DARYLL:
You know, this kid
can fucking fight.

15:53.458 --> 15:55.333
He's just a puncher.

15:55.417 --> 15:57.291
What are you talking about?
He's a beast.

15:57.375 --> 15:59.542
He ain't no real boxer,
that's for sure.

15:59.625 --> 16:01.333
But you don't know
the difference.

16:01.417 --> 16:02.583
I know the difference.

16:02.667 --> 16:04.333
(phone ringing)

16:04.417 --> 16:06.417
You think because you lifted
weights and played football

16:06.500 --> 16:07.583
in high school,
you some type of tough guy.

16:07.667 --> 16:09.709
Yeah, I'm, I'm learning.

16:09.792 --> 16:11.667
Who is this?

16:11.750 --> 16:15.375
SEAN:
I'm sending a car for you
tomorrow at 11:00.

16:15.458 --> 16:16.625
Who is this?

16:16.709 --> 16:18.041
Sean Walker.

16:18.125 --> 16:22.000
Make it 11:30.
I'm drinking tonight.

16:22.083 --> 16:24.417
Okay, that should work.

16:26.291 --> 16:28.625
Whoa! Whoa!

16:30.875 --> 16:34.208
Christ! I'm sleeping over here!

16:34.291 --> 16:38.375
(mocking tone):
Oh, you're sleeping. Oh.

16:38.458 --> 16:41.333
You got a perfectly fine house.

16:41.417 --> 16:42.750
Why ain't you sleeping
over there?

16:42.834 --> 16:46.125
I don't like it no more.

16:46.208 --> 16:47.792
You don't like it no more.

16:47.875 --> 16:49.166
That's all right;
it's just a house. Here.

16:51.959 --> 16:53.250
(laughs)

16:53.333 --> 16:54.667
Stop it, Pa! No.
Ooh. Oh!

16:54.750 --> 16:57.417
(laughs)
Come on.

16:57.500 --> 16:59.041
Get up.
(groaning)

16:59.125 --> 17:00.750
Join the land
of the living.

17:00.834 --> 17:02.291
(groaning)

17:02.375 --> 17:05.542
Come on.
Let's go.

17:05.625 --> 17:07.709
Boxers ain't
fucking tough guys.

17:07.792 --> 17:10.917
They're fucking
students of the sport.

17:11.000 --> 17:12.959
You don't like me, huh?

17:13.041 --> 17:16.750
Was I hiding that
fact from you?

17:16.834 --> 17:18.291
Hey, Terry.

17:18.375 --> 17:20.417
Where's that pretty lady
you been hanging out with?

17:20.500 --> 17:22.125
I haven't seen her
in a while.

17:22.208 --> 17:24.542
She's busy.

17:24.625 --> 17:25.750
(crowd cheering on TV)

17:25.834 --> 17:27.625
He's a puncher.

17:27.709 --> 17:29.500
